# TypeScript/JavaScript Spec-Driven Development Patterns

## Overview
Spec-driven development methodology for TypeScript and JavaScript projects integrating constitutional governance, test-driven specifications, and modern tooling patterns.

## Specification Templates

### TypeScript Interface Specifications
```typescript
/**
 * [SPECIFICATION]: Interface defining core data structure
 * 
 * @specification
 * - Must enforce type safety at compile time
 * - Should provide clear property documentation
 * - Must support JSON serialization/deserialization
 */
interface UserSpecification {
  readonly id: string;
  name: string;
  email: string;
  readonly createdAt: Date;
  preferences?: Record<string, unknown>;
}
```

### Function Specification Pattern
```typescript
/**
 * [SPECIFICATION]: Process user data with validation
 * 
 * @param userData - Input user data to process
 * @returns Promise resolving to processed user
 * 
 * @specification
 * - Input validation: All required fields must be present
 * - Error handling: Must throw UserValidationError for invalid input
 * - Performance: Must complete within 100ms
 * - Output format: Must return UserSpecification-compliant object
 */
async function processUser(
  userData: Partial<UserSpecification>
): Promise<UserSpecification> {
  // Specification validation
  if (!userData.id || !userData.name || !userData.email) {
    throw new UserValidationError('Required fields missing');
  }

  // Implementation satisfying specification
  return {
    id: userData.id,
    name: userData.name.trim(),
    email: userData.email.toLowerCase(),
    createdAt: new Date(),
    preferences: userData.preferences || {}
  };
}
```

## Test-Driven Specifications

### Jest Specification Tests
```typescript
describe('UserProcessor Specification', () => {
  describe('SPECIFICATION: Input validation', () => {
    it('MUST reject input missing required fields', async () => {
      const invalidInput = { name: 'John' };
      await expect(processUser(invalidInput))
        .rejects.toThrow(UserValidationError);
    });
  });

  describe('SPECIFICATION: Performance requirements', () => {
    it('MUST complete within 100ms', async () => {
      const validInput = { id: '123', name: 'John', email: 'john@example.com' };
      const startTime = Date.now();
      await processUser(validInput);
      const duration = Date.now() - startTime;
      expect(duration).toBeLessThan(100);
    });
  });
});
```

## Constitutional Governance

### Project Constitution
```typescript
export const PROJECT_CONSTITUTION = {
  SPECIFICATION_AUTHORITY: {
    principle: 'Specification before implementation',
    enforcement: 'Pre-commit hooks validate specification presence'
  },

  TYPE_SAFETY: {
    principle: 'Strict TypeScript configuration required',
    enforcement: 'No any types without explicit justification'
  },

  TEST_DRIVEN_SPECS: {
    principle: 'Specifications define test requirements',
    enforcement: '100% specification coverage required'
  }
} as const;
```

## Success Metrics

- **Specification Coverage**: 100% of functions have @specification blocks
- **Type Safety**: Zero any types without justification
- **Test Coverage**: 100% of specifications have executable tests
- **Constitutional Compliance**: All code passes validation
